// people.ipt
// =====================================================================
// Reusable PF2e NPC generator. Rolls a person: name, ancestry,
// a one-line description, and a personality beat. Designed to be
// imported (Use:) by the shop files so the same person logic backs
// every shopkeeper, worker, and customer.
//
// Entry tables you can call from other files:
//   [@Person]        - full one-line NPC: "Name, a <desc> <ancestry>"
//   [@PersonName]    - just a name (ancestry-flavoured mix)
//   [@Ancestry]      - just a PF2e ancestry
//   [@Personality]   - a personality trait phrase
//
// PF2e note: ancestries are drawn from the Core Rulebook plus a few
// popular additions (leshy, orc, etc.). Names are deliberately a
// broad fantasy mix rather than strictly per-ancestry naming
// conventions, so any name reads fine with any ancestry. If you want
// strict per-ancestry name lists later, that's a clean extension.

Title: People
Formatting: html

// ---------------------------------------------------------------
// Main entry: a complete person in one line.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------
Table: Person
{!pname==[@PersonName]}{!panc==[@Ancestry]}{$pname}, a [@PersonDesc] {$panc}

// A person with their ancestry available to the caller as variables
// {pname} and {panc} after the call. Useful when a shop wants to
// reuse the same name in a quote.
Table: PersonShort
{$pname}

// ---------------------------------------------------------------
// Names. A broad fantasy mix; first + family.
// ---------------------------------------------------------------
Table: PersonName
[@FirstName] [@FamilyName]

